<TITLE> Visa problem forces coach Nayeemuddin to spend Eid here </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 12 (bdnews24.com)  A visa crisis is compelling Bangladesh's Indian coach Syed Nayeemuddin to celebrate the Eid festival in Bangladesh away from his family members. "I had wished to celebrate Eid with my family members and requested the Bangladesh Football Federation (BFF) to take necessary steps to extend my visa one month ago, but they did not do anything," Nayeemuddin told bdnews24.com Friday. "I am disappointed," said the Indian coach. Nayeemuddin's visa expired on October 5, and the BFF, the day before, applied for extension of his work permit for another four months on multiple entries, a BFF official. BFF protocol officer, Hamiduzzaman Noman, denying Nayeemuddin's allegation, said that the Indian coach had informed them just four days ago. "He (Nayeemuddin) told us about his wishes on October 8 and we tried our best to do the job, but we could not manage a visa despite trying till Thursday, the last working day before the Eid holiday," Noman told bdnews24.com Wednesday. Noman said that they were to submit Nayeemuddin's past six months' income statement, but they had one only for two months following his BFF appointment in August. Before taking over charge of the Bangladesh team, Nayeemuddin coached Brothers Union in the B. League that ended in July. The BFF protocol officer, however, hoped to manage the visa before Bangladesh play their WC pre-qualifier away match against Tajikistan on Oct
